  description: "uuid.UUID.__mro__.__len__()==2 / uuid.UUID.__init__.__code__.co_argcount==7 — UUID.__mro__.__len__() is 2 (uuid.UUID's MRO is (uuid.UUID, object) — 2 classes; UUID is a plain class inheriting only from object; uuid_extra164 anchors UUID.__mro__.__len__()==2; confirmed here under uuidclass165 as a fresh anchor combining with co_argcount); UUID.__init__.__code__.co_argcount is 7 (uuid.UUID.__init__ has 7 positional parameters tracked by co_argcount: self, hex, bytes, bytes_le, fields, int, version; UUID's flexible constructor accepts multiple alternative representations of the same 128-bit value; co_argcount==7 > UUID.__mro__.__len__()==2 by 5 — init takes far more parameters than the MRO has classes; novel anchor: no prior uuid spec anchors UUID.__init__.__code__.co_argcount under uuidclass165; first anchor for this integer value of 7 in the uuid spec family)"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: identity
  id_prefix: uuidclass165

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [uuid_mro_len_2,       "UUID.__mro__.__len__",                  [], 2, "uuid.UUID.__mro__.__len__() is 2 (MRO: (UUID, object); uuid_extra164 anchors; confirmed here under uuidclass165)"]
    - [uuid_init_argcount_7, "UUID.__init__.__code__.co_argcount",    [], 7, "uuid.UUID.__init__.__code__.co_argcount is 7 (self+hex+bytes+bytes_le+fields+int+version; flexible constructor; novel anchor)"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# uuid.NAMESPACE_DNS.__class__.__name__ == 'UUID'
