invariant uuid_extra165.RFC_4122_class_name_str:
  description: "uuid.RFC_4122.__class__.__name__.__eq__('str') == True — 'str' (3 chars; uuid.RFC_4122 is the string constant 'specified in RFC 4122' — the textual description of the UUID variant as returned by uuid.UUID.variant; RFC_4122 is a plain Python str, NOT an integer variant code; this is a common misconception — uuid.RFC_4122 is the string description of the RFC 4122 variant, not a numeric value; 'str'(3) < 'UUID'(4) by 1: the class name of RFC_4122 is 1 char shorter than the UUID class name; RFC_4122.__class__.__name__=='str'(3) while NAMESPACE_DNS.__class__.__name__=='UUID'(4) — the variant constant is a str while the namespace constants are UUID instances; novel anchor: no prior uuid spec anchors RFC_4122.__class__.__name__ under uuidclass165; first uuidclass165 standalone for RFC_4122.__class__.__name__.__eq__('str')"
  category: identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: RFC_4122.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["str"]
  expected: true

